components.description: A group of buttons within a grid layout, having a single callback/event
A group of checkboxes in list format (scrollable if needed)
A color selection control with browse button
A date and time selection control
A file/folder selection control with browse button
A list with configurable buttons alongside. Use the buttons to add, remove, or rearrange the displayed items from a known set. Custom buttons may also be added.
A pair of list controls with configurable buttons alongside. Use the buttons to add items from the left to the right and back or to rearrange the selected items. Custom buttons may also be added.
A password entry field where the text is hidden as dots.
A progress bar that can optionally display time remaining, status message, and cancel button. It can also be made indeterminate to show "busy" status.
A group of sliders paired with checkboxes to enable or disable the slider. (Example usage: adjusting opacity of layers in 2D or 3D graphics.)
A slider and spinner combination for editing and adjusting a scalar numeric value.
A vertical list of tasks with icons to show their status, such as incomplete, complete, error, etc.
A configurable toolbar, similar to the MATLAB toolstrip. Adding sections and controls must be done programmatically. For more information, see WidgetExamples.mlx
